THE TIME CARD MODULE IS AVAILABLE FOR EMPLOYEE
                    USE ON THURSDAY, DECEMBER 14, 2000


Please carefully read the section that applies to you:


Deadline  Due Dates:
Employees & Time Coordinators            - End of business day on Monday,
December 18
Supervisors & Additional Approvers       - End of business day on Tuesday,
December 19


EXEMPT EMPLOYEES :
Exempt employees only have to prepare a time card if they have an absence
to report.
   See your Time Sheet Coordinator for training or you may review the
   instructions by accessing the EOTT Internet Web Page, FAQ's, Payroll,
   Time Card, Time Card Instructions:  How to use the time card.


NON-EXEMPT EMPLOYEES:
All non-exempt employees must turn in a time card for the December 15 pay
period using the EOTT Time Card Module
   Your Time Card Coordinator has been trained to use the new system and
   will train employees who have Internet access or you may review the
   instructions by accessing the EOTT Internet Web Page, FAQ's, Payroll,
   Time Card, Time Card Instructions:  How to use the time card.

   NOTE:  California non-exempt and hourly employees will not use the Time
   Card module; they will submit paper time cards for the year 2000.


   ALL EMPLOYEES:    YOUR LOGON ID IS YOUR SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER.
               YOUR PASSWORD IS YOUR BIRTHDAY IN 8 DIGITS "01011999".
               DO NOT USE DASHES IN THE NUMBERS.
